### 1) Sign up a test user
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/sign-up/email
Content-Type: application/json
origin: http://localhost:3000 

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123",
  "name": "Test User"
}



### 2) Sign in as that user
# IMPORTANT: after this request runs, REST Client will store cookies automatically,
# so the next requests will be authenticated as this user.
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/sign-in/email
Content-Type: application/json
Origin: http://localhost:3000

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "supersecret123"
}



### 3) Check current session (should show logged-in user)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/get-session



### 4) Now call your AI endpoint as LOGGED-IN user (cookies included)

